it feels, yes :) but in fact your visual cortex has some input lag and creates the missing pictures - so you won&#39;t even notice the &quot;steps&quot;

and even if you follow a moving object, there are small steps - but you won&#39;t notice them like you&#39;re doing while scanning over a landscape

you can check this out very easily if you stand yourself in front of a mirror and try to follow your own eye movements or try to see your eyeballs moving while looking at one eye and then at the other - it does not work
